## Context

Eleventh run — web search available. 8 projects all in development (new: ts-developmental-trajectory-modeling). Created 4 journal entries (#1111-1114) and 4 tasks (#812-815).

### Key findings recorded:
- **ts-striatal-interneuron-pathology (journal #1111):** Mesoscale molecular architecture of human striatum (bioRxiv Mar 4, 2026; doi:10.64898/2026.03.04.709715). Slide-tags spatial transcriptomics, 1.1M cells, 19 donors. 6 molecular zones along dorsal-ventral axis. 199 zone-specific DEGs. Dorsal MSNs enriched for plasticity (GRID2IP, GRIN2A), ventral for chaperones/hedgehog. Spatial zonation attenuates with age (88.2% genes). Cross-relevant to cstc-circuit-expression-atlas and ts-developmental-trajectory-modeling.
- **ts-rare-variant-convergence (journal #1112):** Saia et al. clinical exome study NOW PUBLISHED (Frontiers Psychiatry Feb 13, 2026; doi:10.3389/fpsyt.2026.1744145). 80 TS children, 13.7% with causative variants in PNKD, SLC6A1, CACNA1D, BRPF1, KMT2C, SMARCA2, PTEN, RERE. Chromatin remodeling pathway convergence. PC-V patients have worse severity (YGTSS 28 vs 18.5) and lower IQ. Also: BICAN integrated BG epigenomic resource launched at basalganglia.epigenomes.net (cross-species multi-omics).
- **ts-drug-repurposing-network (journal #1113):** MR-based drug target study (Zhou & Li, Italian J Pediatrics 2025; doi:10.1186/s13052-025-02048-x). LAMA5 top druggable gene target for TS. Also RET, CAPNS1. LAMA5 links genetic+immune hypotheses (CD4+ T-cell regulation). 7 methylation sites regulate expression.
- **Monitoring (journal #1114):** Comprehensive status update on all tracked items.

